To Professor Gerald;<br><br>
I am sorry for what you perceive to be my own chest beating. <br>
I've always felt I did the job that was required of me, nothing more. During our reunion I found out things about myself that I did not know and so, I am proud of what I accomplished. <br>
I would say that I opened fire upon the enemy 90% of the time because of the Marines pinned down and the need for fire superiority. <br>
I have here posted what occurred in battle and not for my own glory, its the truth of what occurred. It reflects the war I fought. <br>
If you're looking for further reason I'll refer you to thread #111; Rising above survivor's guilt, <br>
Subtitle; GUILT AND AMERICAN PRIDE! And another response to Ed, subtitle,  MUSTANG TWO FOUR. It will also answer your question about being blown off or called down upon returning at the local Legion or VFW post. But you might see that as more chest beating. <br><br>

